headline: Intuit (INTU): Reviewing Valuation as Stock Momentum Stalls After Multi-Year Rally
summary: Intuit (INTU) has seen shares stay mostly flat today. The stock has lost around 4% over the past month and 15% across the past 3 months. Investors are watching for fresh catalysts that could drive renewed momentum. See our latest analysis for Intuit. Intuit’s momentum has faded since its strong start to the year, with a recent stretch of muted share price movement following several quarters of double-digit growth in both revenue and net income.
